<HEAD>65,000 Stroll Across Chesakpeake Bridge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANDY POINT, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A record 65,000 people walked across the 4.3 mile eastbound span of the <LOCATION> Chesapeake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bridge </LOCATION>. Stollers were met Sunday on the west side by Gov. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Schaefer </PERSON>, who kicked off his One Million Marylanders bay clean-up campaign, an attempt to get residents to practice water conservation and change household disposal habits. The Bay Bridge Walk, which began at 9 a.m. and was completed by 5:30 p.m., drew 15,000 more people this year than last year's record, in part because Sunday was one of the first warm weekend days in what has been a rainy, cool spring The first annual walk was in 1975. `` I'm out here every year because it's here,'' said <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Mary </PERSON>'s resident <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Chesley </PERSON> `` Why you walk across a bridge is the same reason you climb a mountain _ because it's there.''
