LOCATION>, and more than 40 sailors killed. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> casualties were two Marine pilots killed when their AH-1 Cobra helicopter gunship was lost. The Iranians claim they shot it down. Since the clashes in April, the `` rules of engagement'' for <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> ships have been changed so they can intervene in attacks by Iranian vessels on neutral ships in international waters. Iranian speedboats have raided two ships in <LOCATION> Hormuz </LOCATION> in the past week, but there have been no confrontations with the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> since April 18. None of the larger Iranian vessels sighted Monday were involved in that fighting. The only one seen previously, on May 10, was the Alvand, a sister ship of the two frigates hit last month. Western analysts have said the other frigate, <LOCATION> Alborz </LOCATION>, was non-operational but senior <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> officials said recently that both were back on duty.
