<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>Music Makers: A Wide Musical Vocabulary</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HILLEL ITALIE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The songs on <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Dolby </PERSON>'s new album bear little resemblance to the synth-pop sound of his biggest hit, `` She Blinded Me With Science,'' and that's just the way he wants it. Every song I've ever written has been different from every other one,'' Dolby says. `` That's one of my rules of thumb. I like to break ground with every song I write.'' `` Aliens Ate My Buick'' is Dolby's third album. With music ranging from reggae to pop to funk, he hopes no one will identify him with a particular sound. `` That can be a terrible trap to fall into,'' he said. `` I am very fortunate to have a wide musical vocabulary. I can use any musical idiom to make a point.'' Dolby, an Englishman who now lives in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, calls himself a satirist and relates to such musicians as <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Zappa </PERSON> and <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Clinton </PERSON>, whose song `` Hot Sauce'' appears on `` Aliens.'' Dolby pokes fun at men and women, at Americans and especially at himself. `` The songs are like ` <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> Goes </PERSON> to <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>,' a journal of an Englishman who goes to <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' he said in an interview. The first single is called `` Airhead.'' `` The song is about one specific female from first-hand experience,'' he said. `` The big crime is that the lady behaves like an airhead even though she has a brain.'' Dolby's concern about how women would feel about `` Airhead'' was eased when a friend showed him some lyrics for a song called `` Bonehead.'' `` It's about a guy who wears all the right clothes. I read them and I was in fits of hysterics,'' Dolby said. `` It occurred to me, ` Do I feel insulted as a man by these lyrics?' No. They're not about men, they're about a stereotype. It's making fun of the stereotype. `` The only complaints I've had have been from men.'' Dolby has worked with a number of artists, including <PERSON> Joni </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, <PERSON> Joan </PERSON> <PERSON> Armatrading </PERSON>, Foreigner and <PERSON> Def </PERSON> <PERSON> Leppard </PERSON>. He is intrigued by the idea of producing a relatively new artist. `` I'd really like to take a raw talent like <PERSON> Terence </PERSON> <PERSON> Trent </PERSON> <PERSON> D'Arby </PERSON> and mold him. He just does n't have the experience to optimize his talent,'' Dolby said. `` There are a lot of people who are at the top of the strata who are good at optimizing the little talent they have. I'd like to get the opposite side.'' On the `` Aliens'' LP, actor <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Asner </PERSON>'s voice can be heard shouting `` murder'' on `` My Brain Is Like a Sieve.'' <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Leach </PERSON>, the host of television's `` Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous,'' introduces the album's first song, `` Key to Her Ferrari.'' `` I was looking for a good attitude to begin the album,'' Dolby said. `` He -LRB- <PERSON> Leach </PERSON> -RRB- has a production office in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> for ` Lifestyles' so I sent him a tape and he really liked the song.'' `` Aliens'' was produced by Dolby and <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Bittrell </PERSON>, who worked on <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>'s latest album, `` Bad.'' `` They had a good dozen engineers working on that album,'' said Dolby. `` Everybody said the most creative and sweetest to work with was <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Bittrell </PERSON>.'' Dolby's first album, `` The Golden Age of Wireless,'' was released in 1982 and included `` She Blinded Me With Science.'' Dolby toured in 1984 after the release of his second album, `` Flat Earth,'' but had difficulty reproducing the sound from his studio recordings. He does not anticipate that problem when he tours this summer. `` The songs on this album lend themselves a lot more easily to being performed live,'' he said. `` They're a lot more groove-based.'' Dolby will tour with the band he used on `` Aliens.'' Although <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> is famous for having big name session players, Dolby auditioned unknown musicians to play on his new album. `` I was looking to find some people with enthusiasm. The LA lifestyle is not conducive to challenging music,'' he said. `` There are a lot of musicians who are technically proficient but do n't seem to do it with that much conviction `` I was determined to turn up some fresh talent. I wanted people who were good players but had some hunger.'' The success of `` She Blinded Me With Science'' was helped considerably by the accompanying video, which received heavy airplay on Music Television. Dolby says he often writes with visual images in mind. `` I'll have a picture in my head from a magazine or a book, sometimes a scene from a movie,'' Dolby said. `` Sometimes I'm already thinking ahead to the videos.
</TEXT>
