<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The price of gold continued to rise Monday as the dollar drooped slightly against several major currencies in thin trading. <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> said gold was bid at $ 460.30 a troy ounce as of 4 p.m. EDT, up from $ 456.25 an ounce late Friday. Gold has risen more than $ 15 an ounce since early May, partly because the strength of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> economy has raised fears that the economy will become overheated and inflation will rise. Gold was given an additional boost Monday by a big jump in the price of platinum, said <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Koppel </PERSON>, managing director of <ORGANIZATION> Deak </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trading </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> -RRB- Ltd. Platinum jumped $ 17.30 a troy ounce to $ 581.90 an ounce Monday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. That was in reaction to renewed rumors that right-wing elements in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> would succeed in cutting off sales of strategic metals to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Koppel </PERSON> said. Gold has been led upward by buyers from the <LOCATION> Far </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, where unprecedently strong local currencies make gold look like a bargain, said <PERSON> Ian </PERSON> <PERSON> MacDonald </PERSON>, a vice president of <ORGANIZATION> Credit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Suisse </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Moreover, <PERSON> MacDonald </PERSON> said, `` The stock markets have looked so dull and uninteresting, money is clearly com